(a)This release includes certain financial information not derived in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP).
The non-GAAP measure used is free cash flow.
The Company believes that the presentation of this non-GAAP measure provides information that is useful to investors as it indicates more clearly and concisely the amount of cash generated by operations that remains available for payment of debt, share repurchase or dividends after funding capital expenditures, but this information should not be considered a substitute for any measures derived in accordance with GAAP.
The Company manages cash flows available for debt pay down by measuring free cash flow, and includes this measure in all-employee bonus and at-risk compensation bonus targets.
