Section 5  Corporate Governance and Management
Item 5.02  Departure of Directors or Certain Officers; Election of Directors; Appointment of Certain Officers; Compensatory Arrangements of Certain Officers
On August 4, 2009, Buckeye Technologies Inc. (the Company) awarded bonuses to Executive Officers for the fiscal year ended June 30, 2009, based on Compensation Committee approval.  Bonus payments were based on the achievement of cash flow targets set in July 2008.  The Companys receipt of alternative fuel mixture credits was not included in the cash flow calculations for purposes of calculating the bonus awards.  The named Executive Officers will receive the following bonuses.
John B. Crowe, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer, will receive $171,855 based on the Companys At-Risk Compensation bonus (ARC) program and $34,358 from the All Employee bonus plan.
Steven G. Dean, Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer will receive $49,213 based on the Companys ARC program and $14,761 from the All Employee bonus plan.
Kristopher J. Matula, President and Chief Operating Officer, will receive $115,843 based on the Companys ARC program and $23,160 from the All Employee bonus plan.
Paul N. Horne, Senior Vice President, Product Development, will receive $60,620 based on the Companys ARC program and $17,815 from the All Employee bonus plan.
Charles S. Aiken, Senior Vice President, Manufacturing and Sustainability, will receive $82,745 based on the Companys ARC program and $16,543 from the All Employee bonus plan.
 
